EbuCoreFrameRateRatio - Class in edu.harvard.hul.ois.fits
This class handles the creation of a numerator and denominator for a Video Frame Rate, based upon the value passed in, as well as the transformation of actual the value passed in based upon the following logic: If FrameRate from MediaInfo is a whole number, then the following is true: frameRate = the value remains the same numerator = 1 denominator = 1 Otherwise the following is true: frameRate = the value is rounded to the nearest whole integer numerator = 1000 denominator = 1001 For example, if the value passed in is 20, then both the the numerator and denominator are set to 1, and the frame rate is unchanged (20).
